) with 
<taxonomicName id="59874D46836F1F48FF3DF9ECFECEF956" authority="Ruppell, 1830" authorityName="Ruppell" authorityYear="1830" class="Malacostraca" family="Trapeziidae" genus="Trapezia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="50" pageNumber="51" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="guttata">
<emphasis id="ACF3EAD7836F1F48FF3DF9ECFB31F98D" box="[1096,1212,1636,1661]" italics="true" pageId="50" pageNumber="51">T. guttata</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="FA164B34836F1F48FFB3F9ECFECEF956" author="Ruppell" pageId="50" pageNumber="51" refString="Ruppell, E. (1830) Beschreibung und Abbilding von 24 Arten kurzschwanzigen Krabben, als Beitrag zur Naturgeschichte des Rothen Meeres. H. L. Bronner, Frankfurt, 28 pp." type="book" year="1830">
Rüppell, 
<number id="284F24E2836F1F48FA7DF904FECEF956" box="[264,323,1676,1702]" pageId="50" pageNumber="51" value="1830.0">1830</number>
</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
(
<typeStatus id="413C8867836F1F48FA21F904FE05F956" box="[340,392,1676,1702]" pageId="50" pageNumber="51">type</typeStatus>
locality Red Sea) follows from Chen's brief comments and schematic figure. Since the three specimens Chen examined are now lost (see discussion for 
<taxonomicName id="59874D46836F1F48FFF3F93CFA94F93D" box="[1158,1305,1716,1741]" class="Malacostraca" family="Trapeziidae" genus="Trapezia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="50" pageNumber="51" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cymodoce">
