</bibRefCitation>
: 
<number id="284F24E2836E1F49F9E9FECCFD31FEAE" box="[668,700,324,350]" pageId="51" pageNumber="52" value="80.0">80</number>
, pl. 
<number id="284F24E2836E1F49F998FECCFD73FEAE" box="[749,766,324,350]" pageId="51" pageNumber="52" value="2.0">2</number>
, fig. B; pl. 
<number id="284F24E2836E1F49F8F4FECCFC1CFEAE" box="[897,913,324,350]" pageId="51" pageNumber="52" value="4.0">4</number>
) in addition to the spotted ambulatory legs. The red­brown line may fade or it can easily be overlooked in preserved specimens. A light orange carapace and ambulatory legs with orange­red spots is characteristic of 
<taxonomicName id="59874D46836E1F49FA52FE34FD98FE26" authority="Ward, 1941" authorityName="Ward" authorityYear="1941" box="[295,533,444,470]" class="Malacostraca" family="Trapeziidae" genus="Trapezia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="51" pageNumber="52" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="plana">
<emphasis id="ACF3EAD7836E1F49FA52FE34FE0AFE25" box="[295,391,444,469]" italics="true" pageId="51" pageNumber="52">T. plana</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="FA164B34836E1F49FAF8FE34FD98FE26" author="Ward" box="[397,533,444,470]" pageId="51" pageNumber="52" refString="Ward, M. (1941) New Brachyura from the Gulf of Davao, Mindanao, Philippine Islands. American Museum Novitates, 1104, 1 - 15." type="journal article" year="1941">
Ward, 
<number id="284F24E2836E1F49FAAFFE34FD98FE26" box="[474,533,444,470]" pageId="51" pageNumber="52" value="1941.0">1941</number>
</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
(see 
<bibRefCitation id="FA164B34836E1F49F927FE34FD7FFE26" author="Castro" box="[594,754,444,470]" pageId="51" pageNumber="52" refString="Castro, P. (1997 a) Trapeziid crabs (Brachyura: Xanthoidea: Trapeziidae) of New Caledonia, eastern Australia, and the Coral Sea. In: Richer de Forges, B. (Ed.), Les fonds meubles des lagons de Nouvelle-Caledonie (Sedimentologie, Benthos). Etudes et Theses, 3, 59 - 107." type="journal article" year="1997" yearSuffix="a">
Castro 
<number id="284F24E2836E1F49F9D0FE34FD6EFE26" box="[677,739,444,470]" pageId="51" pageNumber="52" value="1997.0">1997</number>
a
</bibRefCitation>
: 
<number id="284F24E2836E1F49F989FE34FC91FE26" box="[764,796,444,470]" pageId="51" pageNumber="52" value="88.0">88</number>
, pl. 
<number id="284F24E2836E1F49F838FE34FCD3FE26" box="[845,862,444,470]" pageId="51" pageNumber="52" value="2.0">2</number>
, fig. D, as 
<taxonomicName id="59874D46836E1F49F8AFFE34FBEBFE25" box="[986,1126,444,470]" class="Malacostraca" family="Trapeziidae" genus="Trapezia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="51" pageNumber="52" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="punctipes">
<emphasis id="ACF3EAD7836E1F49F8AFFE34FC65FE25" box="[986,1000,444,469]" italics="true" pageId="51" pageNumber="52">T</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="ACF3EAD7836E1F49F883FE34FBEBFE25" box="[1014,1126,444,469]" italics="true" pageId="51" pageNumber="52">punctipes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
). Miers' species, however, is undoubtedly 
<taxonomicName id="59874D46836E1F49F95AFE6CFD10FE0D" box="[559,669,484,509]" class="Malacostraca" family="Trapeziidae" genus="Trapezia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="51" pageNumber="52" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="guttata">
<emphasis id="ACF3EAD7836E1F49F95AFE6CFD10FE0D" box="[559,669,484,509]" italics="true" pageId="51" pageNumber="52">T. guttata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as indicated by the straight anterolateral margins of the carapace, postorbital angles that are acute and directed anteriorly, and long cheliped fingers which cross each other when closed (
<bibRefCitation id="FA164B34836E1F49F988FDBCFBBDFDBE" author="Miers" box="[765,1072,564,590]" pageId="51" pageNumber="52" refString="Miers, E. J. (1886) Report on the Brachyura collected by H. M. S. Challenger during the years 1873 - 76. In: Report on the Scientific Results of the Voyage of H. M. S. Challenger During the years 1873 - 76, Zoology, 17 (49). Eyre &amp; Spottiswoode, London, L + 362 pp., pls. 1 - 29." type="book chapter" year="1886">
Miers, 
<number id="284F24E2836E1F49F826FDBCFC1FFDBE" box="[851,914,564,590]" pageId="51" pageNumber="52" value="1886.0">1886</number>
: pl. 
<number id="284F24E2836E1F49F8B0FDBCFC68FDBE" box="[965,997,564,590]" pageId="51" pageNumber="52" value="12.0">12</number>
, fig. 
<number id="284F24E2836E1F49FF57FDBCFBBDFDBE" box="[1058,1072,564,590]" pageId="51" pageNumber="52" value="1.0">1</number>
</bibRefCitation>
). 
<bibRefCitation id="FA164B34836E1F49FF3EFDBCFB6EFDBE" author="Ward" box="[1099,1251,564,590]" pageId="51" pageNumber="52" refString="Ward, M. (1941) New Brachyura from the Gulf of Davao, Mindanao, Philippine Islands. American Museum Novitates, 1104, 1 - 15." type="journal article" year="1941">
Ward (
<number id="284F24E2836E1F49FFEEFDBCFB57FDBE" box="[1179,1242,564,590]" pageId="51" pageNumber="52" value="1941.0">1941</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
, however, was of the opinion that Miers' material belonged to a separate species, to which he applied the name 
<taxonomicName id="59874D46836E1F49FAAFFD0CFD59FD6E" authority="Ward, 1941" authorityName="Ward" authorityYear="1941" box="[474,724,644,670]" class="Malacostraca" family="Trapeziidae" genus="Trapezia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="51" pageNumber="52" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="miersi">
<emphasis id="ACF3EAD7836E1F49FAAFFD0CFDCCFD6D" box="[474,577,644,669]" italics="true" pageId="51" pageNumber="52">T. miersi</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="FA164B34836E1F49F93CFD0CFD59FD6E" author="Ward" box="[585,724,644,670]" pageId="51" pageNumber="52" refString="Ward, M. (1941) New Brachyura from the Gulf of Davao, Mindanao, Philippine Islands. American Museum Novitates, 1104, 1 - 15." type="journal article" year="1941">
Ward, 
<number id="284F24E2836E1F49F9E2FD0CFD59FD6E" box="[663,724,644,670]" pageId="51" pageNumber="52" value="1941.0">1941</number>
</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, without any explanation or examination of Miers' specimens. The material of 
<taxonomicName id="59874D46836E1F49F927FD24FD4EFD35" box="[594,707,684,709]" class="Malacostraca" family="Trapeziidae" genus="Trapezia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="51" pageNumber="52" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="guttata">
<emphasis id="ACF3EAD7836E1F49F927FD24FD4EFD35" box="[594,707,684,709]" italics="true" pageId="51" pageNumber="52">T. guttata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from the 
<collectingCountry id="E6907655836E1F49F84CFD24FC30FD36" box="[825,957,684,710]" name="Philippines" pageId="51" pageNumber="52">Philippines</collectingCountry>
that 
<bibRefCitation id="FA164B34836E1F49F88FFD24FB1DFD36" author="Ward" box="[1018,1168,684,710]" pageId="51" pageNumber="52" refString="Ward, M. (1941) New Brachyura from the Gulf of Davao, Mindanao, Philippine Islands. American Museum Novitates, 1104, 1 - 15." type="journal article" year="1941">
Ward (
<number id="284F24E2836E1F49FF3FFD24FB0AFD36" box="[1098,1159,684,710]" pageId="51" pageNumber="52" value="1941.0">1941</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
had on hand was described as a new species, 
<taxonomicName id="59874D46836E1F49F9F3FD5CFC34FD1E" authority="Ward, 1941" authorityName="Ward" authorityYear="1941" box="[646,953,724,750]" class="Malacostraca" family="Trapeziidae" genus="Trapezia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="51" pageNumber="52" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="davaoensis">
<emphasis id="ACF3EAD7836E1F49F9F3FD5CFCA8FD1D" box="[646,805,724,749]" italics="true" pageId="51" pageNumber="52">T. davaoensis</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="FA164B34836E1F49F858FD5CFC34FD1E" author="Ward" box="[813,953,724,750]" pageId="51" pageNumber="52" refString="Ward, M. (1941) New Brachyura from the Gulf of Davao, Mindanao, Philippine Islands. American Museum Novitates, 1104, 1 - 15." type="journal article" year="1941">
Ward, 
<number id="284F24E2836E1F49F80EFD5CFC34FD1E" box="[891,953,724,750]" pageId="51" pageNumber="52" value="1941.0">1941</number>
</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
. 
<bibRefCitation id="FA164B34836E1F49F8B1FD5CFB3CFD1E" author="Castro" box="[964,1201,724,750]" pageId="51" pageNumber="52" refString="Castro, P. (1997 b) Trapeziid crabs (Brachyura: Xanthoidea: Trapeziidae) of French Polynesia. In: Richer de Forges, B. (Ed.), Les fonds meubles des lagons de Nouvelle-Caledonie (Sedimentologie, Benthos). Etudes et Theses, 3, 109 - 139." type="journal article" year="1997" yearSuffix="b">
Castro (
<number id="284F24E2836E1F49FF54FD5CFBEDFD1E" box="[1057,1120,724,750]" pageId="51" pageNumber="52" value="1997.0">1997</number>
b: 
<number id="284F24E2836E1F49FF0EFD5CFB25FD1E" box="[1147,1192,724,750]" pageId="51" pageNumber="52" value="125.0">125</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
examined two 
<typeStatus id="413C8867836E1F49FA4EFD74FE26FCE6" box="[315,427,764,790]" pageId="51" pageNumber="52">paratypes</typeStatus>
of 
<taxonomicName id="59874D46836E1F49FAA4FD74FDE2FCE5" box="[465,623,764,789]" class="Malacostraca" family="Trapeziidae" genus="Trapezia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="51" pageNumber="52" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="davaoensis">
<emphasis id="ACF3EAD7836E1F49FAA4FD74FDE2FCE5" box="[465,623,764,789]" italics="true" pageId="51" pageNumber="52">T. davaoensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(MNHN­B 
<number id="284F24E2836E1F49F988FD74FCC5FCE6" box="[765,840,764,790]" pageId="51" pageNumber="52" value="16783.0">16783</number>
) and confirmed that it is conspecific with 
<taxonomicName id="59874D46836E1F49FA7DFCACFEF7FCCD" box="[264,378,804,829]" class="Malacostraca" family="Trapeziidae" genus="Trapezia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="51" pageNumber="52" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="guttata">
<emphasis id="ACF3EAD7836E1F49FA7DFCACFEF7FCCD" box="[264,378,804,829]" italics="true" pageId="51" pageNumber="52">T. guttata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. This is also evident from Ward's (
<number id="284F24E2836E1F49F856FCACFCEFFCCE" box="[803,866,804,830]" pageId="51" pageNumber="52" value="1941.0">1941</number>
: fig. 
<number id="284F24E2836E1F49F8D4FCACFC4DFCCE" box="[929,960,804,830]" pageId="51" pageNumber="52" value="27.0">27</number>
) photograph of 
<taxonomicName id="59874D46836E1F49FFF7FCACFAAEFCCD" box="[1154,1315,804,829]" class="Malacostraca" family="Trapeziidae" genus="Trapezia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="51" pageNumber="52" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="davaoensis">
<emphasis id="ACF3EAD7836E1F49FFF7FCACFAAEFCCD" box="[1154,1315,804,829]" italics="true" pageId="51" pageNumber="52">T. davaoensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Both 
<taxonomicName id="59874D46836E1F49FA3FFCC4FDC8FC96" authority="Ward, 1941" authorityName="Ward" authorityYear="1941" box="[330,581,844,870]" class="Malacostraca" family="Trapeziidae" genus="Trapezia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="51" pageNumber="52" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="miersi">
<emphasis id="ACF3EAD7836E1F49FA3FFCC4FE3CFC95" box="[330,433,844,869]" italics="true" pageId="51" pageNumber="52">T. miersi</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="FA164B34836E1F49FACCFCC4FDC8FC96" author="Ward" box="[441,581,844,870]" pageId="51" pageNumber="52" refString="Ward, M. (1941) New Brachyura from the Gulf of Davao, Mindanao, Philippine Islands. American Museum Novitates, 1104, 1 - 15." type="journal article" year="1941">
Ward, 
<number id="284F24E2836E1F49F97DFCC4FDC8FC96" box="[520,581,844,870]" pageId="51" pageNumber="52" value="1941.0">1941</number>
</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, and 
<taxonomicName id="59874D46836E1F49F9F0FCC4FC34FC96" authority="Ward, 1941" authorityName="Ward" authorityYear="1941" box="[645,953,844,870]" class="Malacostraca" family="Trapeziidae" genus="Trapezia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="51" pageNumber="52" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="davaoensis">
<emphasis id="ACF3EAD7836E1F49F9F0FCC4FCA8FC95" box="[645,805,844,869]" italics="true" pageId="51" pageNumber="52">T. davaoensis</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="FA164B34836E1F49F85BFCC4FC34FC96" author="Ward" box="[814,953,844,870]" pageId="51" pageNumber="52" refString="Ward, M. (1941) New Brachyura from the Gulf of Davao, Mindanao, Philippine Islands. American Museum Novitates, 1104, 1 - 15." type="journal article" year="1941">
Ward, 
<number id="284F24E2836E1F49F809FCC4FC34FC96" box="[892,953,844,870]" pageId="51" pageNumber="52" value="1941.0">1941</number>
</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, are therefore junior subjective synonyms of 
<taxonomicName id="59874D46836E1F49FAD3FCFCFD4AFC7E" authority="Ruppell, 1830" authorityName="Ruppell" authorityYear="1830" box="[422,711,884,910]" class="Malacostraca" family="Trapeziidae" genus="Trapezia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="51" pageNumber="52" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="guttata">
<emphasis id="ACF3EAD7836E1F49FAD3FCFCFD9BFC7D" box="[422,534,884,909]" italics="true" pageId="51" pageNumber="52">T. guttata</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="FA164B34836E1F49F968FCFCFD4AFC7E" author="Ruppell" box="[541,711,884,910]" pageId="51" pageNumber="52" refString="Ruppell, E. (1830) Beschreibung und Abbilding von 24 Arten kurzschwanzigen Krabben, als Beitrag zur Naturgeschichte des Rothen Meeres. H. L. Bronner, Frankfurt, 28 pp." type="book" year="1830">
Rüppell, 
<number id="284F24E2836E1F49F9FCFCFCFD4AFC7E" box="[649,711,884,910]" pageId="51" pageNumber="52" value="1830.0">1830</number>
</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
.
